* What's Go good at?

Sweet spot

- Designed with servers and distributed systems in mind
- Replace complex bash scripts
- Anything you'd use any other GC'd language for

If it's your thing

- [[https://github.com/golang/go/wiki/Mobile][Mobile]]
- Desktop - Qt ([[https://github.com/therecipe/qt][1]], [[https://github.com/visualfc/goqt][2]]), [[https://github.com/go-qml/qml][QML]], GTK ([[https://github.com/mattn/go-gtk/][1]], [[https://github.com/gotk3/gotk3][2]])
- [[https://github.com/gopherjs/gopherjs][GopherJS]] transpiler

Use C, C++, or Rust

- A browser engine
- Anything that can't tolerate GC

